{"source_key":"sha256-8e5f2934ed2f4f156fd5f372fc1fcfa4","record_index":107,"record_hash":"sha256:94b6a9ea7d32749a188a37d9545f93ea7bcee10e7689fba477c5d97212f5a724","timestamp":"2026-06-09T14:51:04.210Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"claude:assistant:text","role":"assistant","text":"I've got the whole thing nailed down. Here's what happened.\n\n## Root cause\n\nThe new upstream-integration API (merged today in **[#14107 \"upstream integration: use the new API\"](https://github.com/gitbutlerapp/gitbutler/pull/14107)**) has a bug: **when *every* applied branch is fully integrated upstream, it leaves the managed workspace commit as an orphan with an empty tree** instead of reparenting it onto the new target.\n\nYour situation hit it exactly — you had **two** branches applied, `detect-agent-env-vars` (PR #14129) and `agent-skill-notice-debounce` (PR #14132), and **both** were already merged into master. When you hit \"Update workspace\", the new code (`MergeUpstream` op) removed both integrated parents from the workspace commit and never re-attached it to the target.\n\n### The code bug\n\nIn `crates/but-workspace/src/upstream_integration.rs` (from #14107), the disconnect block:\n\n```rust\n// Disconnect all stack heads from the workspace commit, if any.\nif let Some(workspace_commit_selector) = workspace_commit_selector {\n    for selector in &[REDACTED:entropy] {\n        editor.remove_edges(workspace_commit_selector, *selector)?;  // removes, never re-parents to target\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe sibling `Rebase` path (a few lines down) *does* re-attach to the target via `editor.add_edge(child, target_ref_selector, *removed)`, but this workspace-commit block doesn't. Remove the only branch and the workspace commit survives (this is what the `fully-integrated-branch.sh` fixture tests — *one of two* branches stays). Remove **all** branches and the workspace commit is orphaned → `editor.rebase()` materializes it with the canonical empty tree `4b825dc6…`. **There's no test fixture for the all-branches-integrated case**, which is why it slipped through.\n\n### Evidence chain\n- `HEAD` = `fd97359b78` is a **parentless root commit** with **tree `4b825dc642…`** (canonical empty tree). That's why every file shows as untracked.\n- Logs at `13:54:28Z`: `workspace_integrate_upstream … updates=[Rebase efe312e0, Rebase 882d55b6] dry_run=No` → `safe_checkout current_head_id=d48fead375… new_head_id=fd97359b78…`. It checked the empty-tree orphan out over your real tree (`d48fead375`).\n- The **\"11963 commits behind\"** is `git rev-list --count --first-parent gitbutler/target` = exactly **11963**. With an empty-tree orphan there's no merge-base, so the UI counts the target's entire first-parent history as \"behind.\" Pure cosmetic fallout of the orphan HEAD.\n- The flag `newIntegrateUpstreamModalFeature` (`feature-new-integrate-upstream-modal`) **defaults to `true`**, so nightly `0.5.2062` used the new API automatically — you didn't opt in.\n\n## Your data is safe — recovery\n\nNothing is lost. Your working tree is fully intact on disk, and the oplog has a clean pre-update snapshot:\n\n```\nb0c9e3a398  MergeUpstream   ← the broken op\n241260124e  AmendCommit     ← last good state (both branches in_workspace, valid workspace commit)\n```\n\nSnapshot `241260124e`'s worktree tree is `d48fead375…` — exactly your content from right before the bad checkout. Restore it with:\n\n```\nbut oplog restore [REDACTED:entropy]\n```\n\n(or in-app: Operations history → Undo the \"Merge Upstream\" entry).\n\n**Before you click \"Update workspace\" again**, disable the new path so you use the old (working) integration: Settings → Experimental → turn off the new \"Integrate upstream\" feature (clears `feature-new-integrate-upstream-modal` in localStorage). Then updating is safe — and since both branches are merged, they'll just drop out of the workspace cleanly.\n\n---\n\nTwo things I can do right now — want me to:\n\n1. **Run the recovery** (`but oplog restore 241260124e…`)? I'd want you to **quit GitButler first** — I saw `database is locked` errors in the logs, and restoring while the app holds the SQLite lock will conflict.\n2. **Implement the fix + open a PR** — add the target re-parent when `[REDACTED:entropy]` drains all of the workspace commit's edges, plus a `fully-integrated-all-branches` test fixture covering the gap.\n\nTell me which (or both) and I'll go.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"parentUuid":"[REDACTED:entropy]","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","type":"message","role":"assistant","diagnostics":null,"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3233,"cache_read_input_tokens":88804,"output_tokens":3213,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3233,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":3213,"cache_read_input_tokens":88804,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3233,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3233},"type":"message"}],"speed":"fast"}},"requestId":"[REDACTED:entropy]","type":"assistant","uuid":"[REDACTED:entropy]","timestamp":"2026-06-09T14:51:04.210Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"[REDACTED:entropy]","sessionId":"[REDACTED:entropy]","version":"2.1.165","gitBranch":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}